// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// RULES
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// 1. Emitting BC NEVER imports from consuming BC
// 2. Consuming BC implements the port the emitting BC defines
// 3. Port payloads use primitive types only (string, number, boolean, Record)
// 4. Publisher handler has try/catch — cross-BC failure must not affect emitting BC
// 5. ACL adapter is the only place that knows both models
// 6. Token is a Symbol — no string collision risk
//
// For microservices: replace the adapter body with a message broker publish.
// The port and handler stay the same — only the adapter changes.
